Cell[TextData[{
 "The partial transpose of a Gaussian state is not Hermitian any longer \
although it is still a Gaussian operator. The covariance matrix of the \
partial transpose of a traceless Gaussian operator is simply given by the \
complex conjugate (",
 StyleBox["not",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " Hermitian conjugate) of the original covariance matrix. This is \
demonstrated here."
}], "ExampleText",
 CellID->1449195173,ExpressionUUID->"af12421a-9cc9-4810-9a6f-883a57fd7b29"],

